title: Germany Dada: An alphabet of German Dadaism
description:
Genre/Form: 	Documentary films, Nonfiction films, Interviews

All Authors / Contributors: 	Helmut Herbst; Hans Richter; Richard Huelsenbeck; Cinegraphik (Firm); Universal Education and Visual Arts.; Kartes Video Communications.; Interactive Educational Media.; Educational Video Network, Inc.

Language Note: 	Primarily in English; some portions in German with English subtitles.

Originally produced as a motion picture in 1968.

Credits: 	Documentation, C. Caspari ; animation, Franz Winzentsen.

Abstract:
Deals with aims and activities of the revolutionary group of artists and writers who made up the Dadaist movement in Germany. Filmed in the Dadaist spirit with the cooperation of two original Dadaists, Hans Richter and Richard Huelsenbeck.

Note: This is taken off youtube, so the quality is very lousy, sorry about that. Still, it might be of you to some of you, who are into collecting.
